        "notes": "Table shows additional impact categories beyond EN 15804. Note: The table has duplicate A2 column headers in the Production group (first two columns both labeled A2 Transport). This appears to be a table layout issue in the source document. B4 and B5 columns contain 'MND' (Module Not Declared) values. The table appears to be missing C3 data column in some rows - the column is shown in header but values suggest C3 may have been omitted or zero values collapsed. Also note that C1 column appears to have zero values throughout."
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD_023.0011.007-02.00.00%2520Rockwool%2520Rockfit%2520Mono%2520EN%2520-%2520signed/scenarios",
      "@type": "ScenarioSet",
      "sectionTitle": "10 DETAILS OF THE UNDERLYING SCENARIOS USED TO CALCULATE THE IMPACTS",
      "scenarios": [
        {
          "module": "A1",
          "number": "10.1",
          "title": "A1 - raw material supply",
          "description": "Included. This module considers the extraction and processing of all raw materials and energy which occur upstream to the studied manufacturing process. Raw materials are modelled using primary process data for the stone wool. Literature data for the other components. Recycled content consists of secondary materials from the market and internally recycled materials. Both are modelled without environmental burden, apart from the processing it takes to prepare for on-site recycling."
        },
        {
          "module": "A2",
          "number": "10.2",
          "title": "A2 – transport to the manufacturer",
          "description": "Included. The materials are transported to the manufacturing site using supplier specific distances."
        },
        {
          "module": "A3",
          "number": "10.3",
          "title": "manufacturing",
          "description": "Included. This module considers the production process. The system boundaries include all materials, products and energy, as well as waste processing up to the end-of-waste state or disposal of final residues during the product stage. There are no co-products that have a value of 1% or higher and hence only mineral wool products and wastes leave the facility. In the case of input of secondary materials or energy recovered from secondary fuels, the system boundary between the system under study and the previous system (providing the secondary materials) is set where outputs of the previous system, e.g. materials, products or energy or building elements, reach the end-of-waste stage. No offsetting of CO2 with certificates has been applied. Losses for manufacturing at ROCKWOOL are included."
        },
        {
          "module": "A4",
          "number": "10.4",
          "title": "A4 – transport to the building site",
          "description": "Fuel type and consumption of vehicle or vehicle type used for transport: Truck: Diesel, 1 litre per 3 km, by trailer\nDistance: 171 km\nCapacity utilisation (including empty returns): Truck: 85% delivery; 0% for 30% of empty returns\nBulk density of transported products: Varies from 34 kg/m³ to 105 kg/m³\nVolume capacity utilisation factor: 1 or lower for compressed insulation products\n\nThe products from the Roermond location for the Belgian market are shipped to customers (40%) using 150 km distance to Brussels and through a warehouse (60%) using the same distance plus 35 km for supply to the construction site. The 40:60 ratio has been checked and is representative for ROCKWOOL. The average distance is 171 km. Transportation of the insulation is by truck and is based on volume transportation. Contracted parties confirm a use of 1 litre of diesel per 3 km and a return freight that includes a 25% empty return with the rest being contracted out. The volume depends on the trailer type. ROCKWOOL operates normal trailers (88 m³), mega trailers (95 m³) and combi (105 m³) and load factors are typically high to optimize logistics and reduce cost. For this LCA a relatively small trailer is modelled based on a volume of 88 m³ with a load factor or 85%."
        },
        {
          "module": "A5",
          "number": "10.5",
          "title": "A5 – installation in the building",
          "description": "At the construction site, packaging materials are released. Also 2% material losses have been taken into account.\n\nParts of the installation:\nProcesses necessary for the installation of the product: MANUAL INSTALLATION, SO NO ENERGY CONSUMPTION\nFixation materials: NOT DECLARED\nJointing materials: NONE\nTreatments: NONE\nMaterial losses: 2%\nPackaging: 0.002 KG PALLETS, 0.005 KG FOIL\nOthers:\n\nAncillary materials for installation (specified by material): Insert information\nWater use: None\nOther resource use: None\nQuantitative description of energy type (regional mix) and consumption during the installation process: Manual installation\nWaste materials on the building site before waste processing, generated by the product's installation (specified by type): No ancillary materials declared\nOutput materials (specified by type) as result of waste processing at the building site e.g. of collection for recycling, for energy recovery, disposal (specified by route): Not relevant\nDirect emissions to ambient air, soil and water: None\nDistance: Not relevant"
        },
        {
          "module": "B",
          "number": "10.6",
          "title": "B – use stage (excluding potential savings)",
          "description": "Included. There are no consumables, maintenance, repair, replacements, or refurbishments related to the use of the ROCKWOOL insulation products.\n\nOperational benefits from using insulation material on the building level have not been included as the building performance is unclear without a specific building design. Emissions during use are included.\n\nB1 The free formaldehyde content in the product is the one that could be potentially released through the lifetime of the product and therefore this approach serves as an indication to the figure assigned to module B1. The default value will therefore be 16 mg/kg.\n\nROCKWOOL insulation products for the French market have been tested and obtained a category A+ (très faibles émissions, or very low emissions) rating based on the French \"Plan National Santé Environnement (PNSE)\".\n\nB2 ROCKWOOL products do not require maintenance during use in standard conditions and if correctly applied.\n\nB3 ROCKWOOL building insulation products are hidden from the surface and do not require any cleaning.\n\nB4 ROCKWOOL products will not be replaced during use in standard conditions and if correctly applied; (correctly applied meaning that installed according to ROCKWOOL instructions).\n\nB5 ROCKWOOL products are not refurbished during use in standard conditions and if correctly applied.\n\nB6 and B7 relate to the operations of the building and have therefor not been declared."
        },
        {
          "module": "C",
          "number": "10.7",
          "title": "C: End of life",
          "description": "The deconstruction is manual like the installation. The transportation distances and waste processing and landfill scenarios are identical to the building waste scenario.\n\nMaterials that are landfilled include manual dismantling in module [C1] and transportation in [C2] and emissions from landfilling and incineration in [C4].\n\nModule C2 – Transport to waste processing:\nType of vehicle: Truck\nFuel consumption: 0.37 litres/km\nDistance: 30+100 km (incineration), 30+50 km (landfill)\nCapacity utilisation: 50%\nDensity of products: 35 kg/m³\n\nEnd-of-life modules – C3 and C4:\nWastes collected separately: 0 kg\nWastes collected as mixed construction waste: 100 kg\nWaste for re-use: 0 kg\nWaste for recycling: 0 kg\nWaste for energy recovery: 50 kg\nWaste for final disposal: 50 kg"
        },
        {
          "module": "D",
          "number": "10.8",
          "title": "D – Benefits and loads beyond the system boundaries",
          "description": "Information module D aims at transparency for the environmental benefits or loads resulting from reusable products, recyclable materials and/or useful energy carriers leaving a product system, e.g. as secondary materials or fuels. Any declared benefits and loads from net flows leaving the product system that have not been allocated as co-products and that have passed the end-of-waste state are included in module D. This includes the waste from [A3] that is recycled and the packaging from [A5]. There are no benefits associated with the ROCKWOOL products themselves declared under module D.\n\nQUANTITATIVE DESCRIPTION OF THE LOADS BEYOND THE SYSTEM BOUNDARIES:\nWood that is burned is treated as thermal waste treatment and not energy recovery as the efficiency is less than 60%. The heat recovery is modelled as part of module [D]. When wood is combusted, the renewable energy is consumed, part of the energy is recovered, and the biogenic carbon is released as carbon dioxide. The recovery is modelled using the lower heating value of 13.99 MJ/kg and a production of heat of 20% and electricity of 10% using the process for heat production: \"Thermal energy from natural gas\" (e.g. Heat, natural gas, at industrial furnace > 100kW) and for electricity production: Belgian high voltage consumption mix, excluding the impact from the transmission network."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD_023.0011.007-02.00.00%2520Rockwool%2520Rockfit%2520Mono%2520EN%2520-%2520signed/references",
      "@type": "Bibliography",
      "bibliography": [
        "ISO 14040:2006: Environmental Management-Life Cycle Assessment-Principles and framework.",
        "ISO 14044:2006: Environmental Management-Life Cycle Assessment-Requirements and guidelines.",
        "ISO 14025:2006: Environmental labels and Declarations-Type III Environmental Declarations-Principles and procedures.",
        "NBN EN 15804+A2:2019",
        "B-EPD-PCR",
        "EN13162+A1:2015 Thermal insulation products for buildings. Factory made mineral wool (MW) products. Specification, 4.2.1",
        "EN12667:2000 Thermal performance of building materials and products - Determination of thermal resistance by means of guarded hot plate and heat flow meter methods - Products of high and medium thermal resistance.",
        "EN12939:2001 Thermal performance of building materials and products. Determination of thermal resistance by means of guarded hot plate and heat flow meter methods. Thick products of high and medium thermal resistance.",
        "EN13162+A1:2015 Thermal insulation products for buildings. Factory made mineral wool (MW) products. Specification, 4.3.15"
      ]
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD_023.0011.007-02.00.00%2520Rockwool%2520Rockfit%2520Mono%2520EN%2520-%2520signed/sections",
      "@type": "EpdSectionSet",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "number": "11.1",
          "title": "Indoor air",
          "content": "SUBSTANCES TO INDOOR AIR,\n\nSOIL AND WATER DURING THE\n\nUSE STAG E\n\nThe European Regulation (CE) n° 1272/2008 onclassification, labelling and packaging of substances and mixtures updated\n\nby the Regulation (CE) n°790/2009 does not classify mineral wool fibres as a dangerous substance as long as they fulfil\n\ncriteria defined in its Note Q. The European Certification Board for mineral wool products, EUCEB, certify mineral wool\n\nproducts made of fibres are fulfilling Note Q.www.euceb.org. The product subject of this EPD has a certificate demonstrating\n\ncompliance to Note Q. According to IARC, mineral wool insulating products are not classifiable as to carcinogenicity in\n\nhumans (group 3). The fibers are only to be expected to be released when the product is handled, during installation. Once\n\ninstalled there are is no release of fibres.\n\nROCKWOOL insulation products for the French market have been tested and obtained a category A+ (très faibles émissions,\n\nor very low emissions). The product subject of this EPD emits formaldehyde in concentrations < 0.0016% which is way below\n\nthe CLP threshold of 0,1%."
        },
        {
          "number": "11.2",
          "title": "Soil and water",
          "content": "The European Regulation (CE) n° 1272/2008 onclassification, labelling and packaging of substances and mixtures updated\n\nby the Regulation (CE) n°790/2009 does not classify mineral wool fibres as a dangerous substance as long as they fulfil\n\ncriteria defined in its Note Q. The European Certification Board for mineral wool products, EUCEB, certify mineral wool\n\nproducts made of fibres are fulfilling Note Q.www.euceb.org. The product subject of this EPD has a certificate demonstrating\n\ncompliance to Note Q. According to IARC, mineral wool insulating products are not classifiable as to carcinogenicity in\n\nhumans (group 3). The fibers are only to be expected to be released when the product is handled, during installation. Once\n\ninstalled there are is no release of fibres.\n\nROCKWOOL insulation products for the French market have been tested and obtained a category A+ (très faibles émissions,\n\nor very low emissions). The product subject of this EPD emits formaldehyde in concentrations < 0.0016% which is way below\n\nthe CLP threshold of 0,1%.\n\nThere are no emissions to soil and water during the use stage."
        },
        {
          "number": "12",
          "title": "DEMONSTRATION OF VERIFICATION",
          "content": "11 RELEASE OF DANGEROUS\n\nSUBSTANCES TO INDOOR AIR,\n\nSOIL AND WATER DURING THE\n\nUSE STAG E\n\n11.1 Indoor air\n\nThe European Regulation (CE) n° 1272/2008 onclassification, labelling and packaging of substances and mixtures updated\n\nby the Regulation (CE) n°790/2009 does not classify mineral wool fibres as a dangerous substance as long as they fulfil\n\ncriteria defined in its Note Q. The European Certification Board for mineral wool products, EUCEB, certify mineral wool\n\nproducts made of fibres are fulfilling Note Q.www.euceb.org. The product subject of this EPD has a certificate demonstrating\n\ncompliance to Note Q. According to IARC, mineral wool insulating products are not classifiable as to carcinogenicity in\n\nhumans (group 3). The fibers are only to be expected to be released when the product is handled, during installation. Once\n\ninstalled there are is no release of fibres.\n\nROCKWOOL insulation products for the French market have been tested and obtained a category A+ (très faibles émissions,\n\nor very low emissions). The product subject of this EPD emits formaldehyde in concentrations < 0.0016% which is way below\n\nthe CLP threshold of 0,1%.\n\n11.2 Soil and wate r\n\nThere are no emissions to soil and water during the use stage.\n\nVERIFICATION\n\nEN 15804+A2serves as the core PCR.\n\nIndependent verification of theenvironmental declaration and data according to standard EN ISO 14025:2010.\n\nInternal☐ External☒\n\nThird party verifier:Agnes Schuurmans, SGS INTRON, Dr. Nolenslaan 126, 6136 GV Sittard,agnes.schuurmans@sgs.com"
        },
        {
          "number": "14",
          "title": "ADDITIONAL INFORMATION ON REVERSIBILITY",
          "content": "13 APPLICATION UNIT\n\nPRODUCT DESCRIPTIONREFERENCE THICKNESS SCALABILITY SCALABILITYSPECIFICATIONSAPPLICATION RATIO\n\nMAXIMUM (MM)\n\nFLOW (MM) MINIMUM(MM)\n\nEuro Class A1; unit\n\nmineral wool,\n\nCavity walls;\n\nRockfit load35kg/m³,\n\n600x1000mm, 1m² 150 40 250 curtain walls;1m² 1\n\nMono R=4.25; no facing;\n\nD\n\nseparating walls\n\nλ0.035W/m.K\n\nloss of ignition =3.2\n\nSimplicity of Ease of handling (sizeRobustness of material (material\n\nDescription Type of fixing Level of reversibility Speed of disassembly Comment\n\ndisassembly and weight) resistance to disassembly)\n\nEasy to manipulate (by\n\nInsulation of masonryFixedwith cavity ties andReversible connectionsSimple–no specific hand (small size and\n\nSpeedy disassembly Disassembly is possible but should be done\n\ncavity walls with partial orclips (components to bewith non-repairable dismantling tools required limited weight): one\n\ncarefully in order not to generate any damage\n\nfull cavity fillingadded) damage worker should be\n\nsufficient"
